abstract: Corinna da Fonseca-Wollheim reviews Orazio Vecchi's madrigal comedy L’Amfiparnaso, performed by vocal ensemble Western Wind and mimes Catherine Gasta and Alexander Reed, at West End Theater.
lead_paragraph: The vocal ensemble tackled Orazio Vecchi’s madrigal comedy at the West End Theater, and attempted to soften some its more dated humor.

headline.main: Review: The Western Wind Performs ‘L’Amfiparnaso’ at a Distance
headline.print_headline: Comedy Rendered in Song, Mime and Tempered Tones
